## Your Tools

### Core Pipeline
- `tools/discord_redis_consumer.py` — reads Discord messages from the centralised Redis stream (persistent daemon)
- `tools/inference.py` — runs the trained ML model on a new signal
- `tools/enrich_single.py` — adds real-time market data to a signal (200+ features)
- `tools/risk_check.py` — validates trade against risk limits and daily caps
- `tools/decision_engine.py` — orchestrates the full signal → trade pipeline
- `tools/log_paper_trade.py` — records hypothetical paper trades (NO real orders)

### Analysis & Monitoring
- `tools/technical_analysis.py` — performs TA (RSI, MACD, support/resistance, patterns)
- `tools/options_analysis.py` — options flow and Greeks analysis
- `tools/position_monitor.py` — monitors open positions with trailing stops and partial exits
- `tools/portfolio_tracker.py` — tracks open positions and P&L
- `tools/pre_market_analyzer.py` — runs pre-market analysis and sets agent mode

### Reporting
- `tools/report_to_phoenix.py` — reports activity and metrics to Phoenix dashboard

## Operation Loop

### Pre-Market (9:00 AM ET)
1. Run `python tools/pre_market_analyzer.py` to analyse overnight futures, VIX, economic calendar
2. Set agent mode (aggressive/conservative) based on market context
3. Report market context to Phoenix

### Market Hours — Signal Processing
1. Consume Discord signals from the centralized Redis stream (the API service runs the
   single Discord client and publishes to Redis):
   `python tools/discord_redis_consumer.py --config config.json --output pending_signals.json`
2. When a trade signal is detected (written to `pending_signals.json`):
   a. Parse the signal (ticker, price, direction, option details)
   b. Run `python tools/enrich_single.py --signal pending_signals.json` for 200+ market attributes
   c. Run `python tools/inference.py --features enriched_signal.json` for model prediction
   d. Check rules: evaluate signal against learned rules — compute weighted score
   e. Run `python tools/risk_check.py --signal enriched_signal.json` for position limits
   f. If confidence > threshold AND risk approved AND rule score positive:
      - Run `python tools/technical_analysis.py` for TA confirmation
      - **Log paper trade** via `python tools/log_paper_trade.py --signal enriched_signal.json --direction <DIR> --ticker <TICKER>`
      - Report trade to Phoenix via `tools/report_to_phoenix.py`
   g. If rejected: log the full reasoning to Phoenix

### Position Monitoring (Background Loop)
Run `python tools/position_monitor.py --config config.json` as a background daemon. It handles:
3. Every 60 seconds: check prices via market data tools, update trailing stops
4. Every 5 minutes: run full technical analysis on each open position
5. Every 15 minutes: re-evaluate conviction using RSI, MACD, volume, and news sentiment
6. Partial exit ladder: close 30% at +20%, 50% at +30%, remaining on trailing stop (paper only — log via log_paper_trade.py)
7. TA-based decisions: if RSI > 70 + MACD bearish → exit; if RSI < 70 + MACD bullish → hold
{% if knowledge and knowledge.analyst_profile and knowledge.analyst_profile.is_swing_trader %}
8. Swing trade support: do NOT auto-close positions at EOD if analyst is a swing trader
9. Overnight positions: reduce by 30% before close if unrealised P&L < 5%
{% else %}
8. End of day: log all 0DTE position closes before 3:55 PM ET via log_paper_trade.py
{% endif %}

### End of Day
- Log all intraday position closes via `python tools/log_paper_trade.py`
- Generate daily P&L summary using portfolio_tracker.py
- Report all metrics to Phoenix
- Reset daily counters

